Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @courgette{1}, then slice into thick 1cm rounds. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour. Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @?pepper{} if you'd like, then transfer the courgette 'planets' to a #bowl{}.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the courgette 'planets' have been set aside, wipe out the frying pan and pop back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, then add the @tomato passata{1}, @water{50%ml} for the sauce, @vegetable stock paste{10}, and @?sugar{1/2%tsp} (if you'd like). Stir together, then bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{99.99%g} and half the Cheddar, then simmer until melted and smooth, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if you'd like.

While the sauce simmers, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Chop half your courgette 'planets' into quarters, then stir into the creamy sauce along with the @peas{120%g} and cooked pasta. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Transfer your pasta to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the remaining courgette 'planets'. Sprinkle over the remaining Cheddar to make the stars of your galaxy!

Grill until bubbling and golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Space Ranger Mission: Chart a course for a brand new galaxy! Little space rangers can help decorate the top of the pasta with the courgette 'planets' and cheese 'stars'. Make small piles of cheese here and there to make extra cheesy star clusters.

Meanwhile, put the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} in a bowl with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if you'd like, then mix together.

When ready, share your starry 'galaxy' pasta bake between #bowls{}. Add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the balsamic dressing and toss to coat, then serve alongside. Enjoy!